title: Disabled and Homeless in the USA (Living on $800 a Month with a Painful Skin Condition)

media:group.media:title: Disabled and Homeless in the USA (Living on $800 a Month with a Painful Skin Condition)
media:group.media:description:
Sentaces is disabled and homeless. Her rare skin condition causes open wounds on every part of her body. Sentaces receives $800 a month that mostly goes to live-saving medicine. She is anxious to share her story, but wants others to know the truth about being disabled in the USA.

Sentaces diagnosis is epidermolytic hyperkeratosis ichthyosis bullosa.

We created a PO Box for Sentaces. The address is:
1345 N Jefferson St. # 389 
Milwaukee, WI
53202-2657

Connect with Sentaces at https://www.instagram.com/Serena_beautty/

Sentaces told me she has never received mail and hopes people will take the time to write her. Some products that would be useful to her are Aquaphor, Eczema body wash , Baby oil (cocoa butter), Vaseline , Shea butter, cocoa butter gel, clothes preferably large or 1 x clothes, detergents or clothe strips.
